---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="So Far - Morris Liu">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif mb-6 leading-tight">So Far</h1>
      <nav class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
        <a href="#work" class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Work</a>
        <a href="#skills" class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Skills</a>
        <a href="#projects" class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Projects</a>
        <a href="#side" class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Side</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section id="work" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif mb-4 leading-tight">Work</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Full-Stack Engineer</h3>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Yuanxiang Technology • May 2024 - Present</p>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Leading AI infrastructure architecture and building observability systems with Kubernetes, 
            Prometheus, and Grafana. Optimized RAG technology stack, reducing memory consumption by 90% 
            and improving data pipeline efficiency from hours to minutes.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">CTO</h3>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Gongzhiyi Technology • Sep 2021 - May 2024</p>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Built and led a 20-person engineering team from startup to scale. Architected two core products: 
            a Git-based CAD version control system and a lightweight 3D visualization engine. 
            Established 14-day release cycles and quality assurance processes.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Frontend Engineer</h3>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Meituan • Jul 2018 - Jan 2019</p>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Developed data analytics modules and multi-store management systems. 
            Built component libraries and solved complex browser compatibility issues.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="skills" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif mb-4 leading-tight">Skills</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Languages</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Rust, TypeScript, Go, Python. I believe in type safety and systems that don't surprise you.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Infrastructure</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Kubernetes, Docker, Prometheus, Grafana. Building systems that scale and stay observable.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Data & Web</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Postgres, Redis, React, Tauri. From databases to user interfaces, 
            I enjoy crafting experiences that feel natural.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Leadership</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Built and managed engineering teams up to 20 people. I believe the best 
            technical solutions come from understanding both code and people.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="projects" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif mb-4 leading-tight">Projects</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Sealbox</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            A simple secret storage service built with Rust. Self-hosted and developer-friendly, 
            because managing secrets shouldn't be a secret science.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">openrouter-rs</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Type-safe SDK for OpenRouter.ai in Rust. Making LLM API interactions 
            predictable and pleasant to work with.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Kira</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            An AI-powered second brain currently in development. 
            Designed to catch thoughts before they fade—because the best ideas 
            usually arrive at the worst times.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">CAD Systems</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Built Git-based version control for CAD files and a lightweight 3D visualization engine. 
            Solving the problem of "which version of this design are we looking at?"
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="side" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif mb-4 leading-tight">Side</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          I play bass guitar and listen to jazz, funk, and rock. Music helps me think 
          differently about rhythm and structure—useful skills for both code and life.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          My bio says I'm from Mars, which isn't entirely untrue. I'm fascinated by 
          how things are put together, whether it's a distributed system or a good bassline.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          I believe in building things that last, writing code that others can understand, 
          and occasionally wondering if we're all just elaborate functions in some cosmic program.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif mb-4 leading-tight">Contact</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          You can find me on <a href="https://github.com/realmorrisliu" style="color: var(--color-text-link);">GitHub</a> 
          where I share code and occasionally wonder if anyone reads commit messages.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          For more immediate thoughts and updates, I'm on 
          <a href="https://twitter.com/realmorrisliu" style="color: var(--color-text-link);">Twitter</a>.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          For everything else, email works well: 
          <a href="mailto:morrisliu1994@outlook.com" style="color: var(--color-text-link);">morrisliu1994@outlook.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <!-- 信件结尾式返回链接 -->
    <footer class="mt-16 pt-8">
      <p class="text-base font-serif" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <a href="/" style="color: var(--color-text-link);">Morris Liu</a>
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>
